description:
&lt;p&gt;Applications are invited for Consultant Renal Physicians to work within the department of Renal Services in the Division of Surgery and Tertiary Medicine. There are 2 posts available (1 x substantive and 1 x locum)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Salford Royal NHS Foundation Trust (SRFT) incorporates a large teaching hospital as well as a range of community services. It is a centre of excellence providing specialist and tertiary services on a sub-regional, regional and supra-regional basis as well as secondary care and community services to the local population.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Renal Services are part of a Managed Clinical Network in Greater Manchester and Salford Royal Hospital is the renal centre for the North Sector, which includes Salford, Oldham, Rochdale, Bury, Wigan, Bolton and parts of Trafford. Manchester Royal Infirmary is the renal centre for the South Sector. The 16 WTEs Consultants provide outreach clinics at or close to all District General Hospitals in the North Sector in addition to their Salford Royal clinic commitments. Renal Services has 5 dialysis units based at Salford, Bolton, Wigan, Rochdale and Oldham. The Renal Department has an international research reputation which is supported by a wide portfolio of research which includes clinical trials as well as academic studies.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will have an excellent track record in your field and be able to work effectively as part of a multi-disciplinary team. You will need to have strong leadership and communication skills coupled with a burning desire to improve and succeed. In return, you will benefit from working in a high performing organisation in which you will be able to enhance your skills further.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Please note job plans are subject to change following departmental reviews.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;In line with the Trust’s Single Equality Scheme we welcome applications from everyone irrespective of ethnic origin, disability, age, gender, sexual preference, disability, nationality, religion, marital status, social back ground or trade union membership. However, as members of ethnicity minority groups, individuals with disabilities and women are currently under-represented at this level of post, we would encourage applications from members of these groups. Appointment will be based on merit alone.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Dr Dimitris Poulikakos, Consultant Nephrologist and Clinical Director for Renal Services&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;dimitrios.poulikakos@srft.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;0161 206 5469&lt;/p&gt;
